          "name": "How is stamp duty calculated on a leave and licence agreement in Maharashtra?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Stamp duty on a leave and licence agreement is charged at 0.25 percent of the total consideration for the term, taken as the aggregate rent for the whole period plus any non-refundable deposit and a notional 10 percent per year on the interest-free refundable deposit. On rent of Rs 30,000 a month for 11 months, duty works out to roughly Rs 825 plus the deposit element."
          }
