            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "An insufficiently stamped instrument is not admissible as evidence in court or before an authority until the deficient duty and a penalty are paid, under Section 34 of the Maharashtra Stamp Act 1958. Penalty runs at 2 percent a month on the deficit, capped at four times the deficient duty. The document itself is not void, but it cannot be relied on until it is impounded and regularised."
